race.comment: MRS HARRIS (10) resumes for the McEvoy stable off two placed efforts. Has jumped out well and kicking off at a mile shouldn't be an issue. Draws inside and Coffey's engagement suggests she's pleasing. OUR PIERRO (12) was beaten 1L over a mile at Yarra Valley on debut. Has been well educated and should go close with the extra fitness. CONTOURS (5) is an improver in the premier stable. Needs a good ride from a wide gate but has the blinkers applied for the first time and the step up in distance will suit. Stablemate SMOKIN' GENIE (13) has been disappointing but is likely respond to the addition of blinkers and the extra distance. LIBBY ANN (8) has a tricky gate but is racing well and is in the mix.
